<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8">
		<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=Edge">

		<title>Tools to counter disinformation</title>
		<meta name="description" content="The Office of the French Ambassador for Digital Affairs builds tools to counter information manipulations that aim to disrupt social cohesion and electoral processes.">

		<link rel="shortcut icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico">
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
		<noscript>
			<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0; URL=/fr">
		</noscript>
	</head>

	<body class="landing">
		<script>
			const lang = navigator.language || navigator.userLanguage;

			if (lang.includes('fr')) {
				window.location = '/fr';
			} else if (lang.includes('zh')) {
				window.location = '/zh-Hant';
			} else {
				window.location = '/en';
			}
		</script>

		<h2>You should be redirected to the page with the most appropriate language given by your browser.</h2>

		<p>If this does not happen automatically, you can go to the <a href="/en">English version</a> directly.</p>

